\verb{$render()} produces a string of the form
\verb{mult= replic \{replications\} hold \{hold_rep\} [no]keepall;}
(or \verb{mult:} when \verb{$set_only} is \code{TRUE}).
}

\subsection{Set-only mode}{

When \verb{$set_only} is \code{TRUE}, the command configures parameters in TNT
without triggering a search. This is used internally by
\link{ExtraSearchMethodsCommand} when orchestrating multiple strategies.
}

\subsection{Queue integration}{

Calling \verb{$enqueue()} adds this command to a \link{CommandQueue} and, when
\verb{$set_only} is \code{FALSE}, also enqueues a \link{CollapseTreesCommand} and a
\link{TreePlottingCommand} as follow-up steps.
}
